Up on the balcony!
Come on! Quickly!

7
00:01:51,555 --> 00:01:54,351
Just read them
the sentence!

8
00:01:57,081 --> 00:01:58,968
The sentence of the court...

9
00:01:59,281 --> 00:02:01,095
is that in two days hence...

10
00:02:01,591 --> 00:02:05,628
the perfumer journeyman:
Jean-Baptiste Grenouille...

11
00:02:06,212 --> 00:02:08,453
shall be bound
to a wooden cross...

12
00:02:08,643 --> 00:02:11,667
with his face raised
towards heaven!

13
00:02:13,124 --> 00:02:15,236
And whilst still alive...

14
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:19,455
be dealt twelve blows
with an iron rod...

15
00:02:21,768 --> 00:02:24,587
breaking the joints
of his arms...

16
00:02:25,783 --> 00:02:26,695
his shoulders...

17
00:02:27,457 --> 00:02:28,787
his hips...

18
00:02:29,504 --> 00:02:31,173
his legs!

19
00:02:32,407 --> 00:02:36,469
He shall then be raised up
to hang until dead.

20
00:02:36,983 --> 00:02:40,143
And all customary acts of mercy...

21
00:02:40,251 --> 00:02:43,161
are expressly forbidden
the executioner.

22
00:02:51,805 --> 00:02:54,003
In 18th century France...

23
00:02:54,104 --> 00:03:00,011
there lived a man who was one of the most gifted
and notorious personages of his time.

24
00:03:00,453 --> 00:03:03,373
His name was
Jean-Baptiste Grenouille.

25
00:03:04,075 --> 00:03:08,174
And if his name has been forgotten today,
it is for the sole reason...

26
00:03:08,215 --> 00:03:11,089
that his entire ambition
was restricted to a domain...

27
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:14,838
that leaves no trace in history:

28
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:21,178
to the fleeting realm of scent.

29
00:03:21,179 --> 00:03:26,750
PERFUME
The Story of a Murderer

30
00:03:34,388 --> 00:03:36,364
In the period of which we speak...

31
00:03:36,465 --> 00:03:41,983
there reigned in the cities a stench
barely conceivable to us modern men and women.

32
00:03:43,058 --> 00:03:46,032
Naturally, the stench
was foulest in Paris...

33
00:03:46,067 --> 00:03:49,008
for Paris was
the largest city in Europe.

34
00:03:49,459 --> 00:03:52,738
And nowhere in Paris was that stench
more profoundly repugnant...

35
00:03:52,839 --> 00:03:55,023
than in the city's fish market.

36
00:03:56,586 --> 00:03:59,867
Here we are.
I'll get another box.

37
00:04:00,551 --> 00:04:04,518
It was here then,
on the most putrid spot in the whole kingdom...

38
00:04:04,666 --> 00:04:07,142
that Jean-Baptiste Grenouille was born...

39
00:04:07,145 --> 00:04:09,938
on the 17th of July, 1738.

40
00:04:33,285 --> 00:04:35,178
It was his mother's fifth birth.

41
00:04:35,527 --> 00:04:38,217
She delivered them all here
under her fish stand.

42
00:04:38,321 --> 00:04:40,868
And all had been stillbirths,
or semi-stillbirths.

43
00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:42,042
Are you alright?

44
00:04:42,993 --> 00:04:45,511
And by evening, the whole mess
had been shoveled away...

45
00:04:45,581 --> 00:04:47,301
with the fish guts
into the river.

46
00:04:48,053 --> 00:04:49,951
It would be much the same today...

47
00:04:50,738 --> 00:04:52,158
but then...

48
00:04:52,746 --> 00:04:55,559
Jean-Baptiste chose differently.

49
00:05:27,989 --> 00:05:29,144
What's that noise?

50
00:05:29,774 --> 00:05:31,575
It's... it's a baby.

51
00:05:31,576 --> 00:05:32,882
What's going on here?

52
00:05:36,719 --> 00:05:39,502
- It's a newborn.
- Where's his mother?

53
00:05:40,952 --> 00:05:42,160
She was just here.

54
00:05:44,634 --> 00:05:49,810
She tried to kill it, her own child.
She tried to kill a baby!

55
00:05:51,628 --> 00:05:53,225
There! There she is!

56
00:05:53,476 --> 00:05:55,941
- Stop! Stop where you are!
- Murderer!

57
00:05:56,026 --> 00:05:59,554
Thus, the first sound
to escape Grenouille's lips...

58
00:06:00,137 --> 00:06:01,815
sent his mother
to the gallows.

59
00:06:05,609 --> 00:06:08,157
And Jean-Baptiste,
by official order...

60
00:06:09,049 --> 00:06:11,335
to the orphange
of Madame Gaillard.

61
00:06:14,417 --> 00:06:19,397
- How many today?
- Four, well... three and a half.

62
00:06:23,345 --> 00:06:28,744
