00:35:42,081 --> 00:35:44,616
Because talent means
next to nothing!

252
00:35:46,752 --> 00:35:49,251
While experience, acquired in humility...

253
00:35:49,762 --> 00:35:53,038
and hard work, means everything.

254
00:35:57,294 --> 00:35:59,765
I don't, I don't know
what a formula is.

255
00:35:59,967 --> 00:36:02,797
But I can make
"Amor and Psyche" for you now.

256
00:36:04,084 --> 00:36:07,158
And you think I'll just let you
slop around in my laboratory...

257
00:36:07,259 --> 00:36:09,153
with essential oils
that are worth a fortune?

258
00:36:09,489 --> 00:36:10,400
You?

259
00:36:11,506 --> 00:36:13,921
- Yes.
- Now pay attention!

260
00:36:17,172 --> 00:36:18,581
What is your name, anyway?

261
00:36:20,535 --> 00:36:22,217
Jean-Baptiste Grenouille.

262
00:36:24,975 --> 00:36:27,343
Very well, Jean-Baptiste Grenouille.

263
00:36:29,096 --> 00:36:32,371
You shall have the opportunity now,
this very moment, to prove your assertion.

264
00:36:32,424 --> 00:36:35,460
Your grandiose failure will also be
an opportunity for you to learn...

265
00:36:35,506 --> 00:36:38,697
- the virture of humility.
- How much do you want me to make?

266
00:36:38,747 --> 00:36:42,137
- How much of... what?
- How much "Amor and Psyche" do you want?

267
00:36:44,837 --> 00:36:48,667
- Shall I fill this flask?
- No! You shall not!

268
00:36:57,644 --> 00:37:00,206
- You may fill this one.
- Yes, master.

269
00:37:03,125 --> 00:37:05,254
- But, Master Baldini,
- Hmm?

270
00:37:05,598 --> 00:37:08,160
you must let me do it
in my own way.

271
00:37:08,610 --> 00:37:10,377
As you please.

272
00:37:16,608 --> 00:37:18,847
Don't drop that!
That's pure alcohol!

273
00:37:18,919 --> 00:37:21,061
You want to blow up
the entire building?

274
00:37:23,503 --> 00:37:25,132
You have to measure it first!

275
00:38:12,144 --> 00:38:15,456
Stop! Stop it!
That's enough! Basta!

276
00:38:15,841 --> 00:38:17,075
You know nothing!

277
00:38:17,546 --> 00:38:22,045
Essential oils are always to be
mixed first, then the alcohol added.

278
00:38:22,100 --> 00:38:25,225
And never ever let this perfume
to be shaken like that.

279
00:38:25,511 --> 00:38:28,697
I must've been insane
to listen to your asinine gibberish.

280
00:38:30,555 --> 00:38:32,115
Yes, we're done.

281
00:39:00,745 --> 00:39:02,375
Mamamiya...

282
00:39:16,194 --> 00:39:18,424
This is "Amor and Psyche".

283
00:39:19,231 --> 00:39:21,484
But it's not a good perfume, master.

284
00:39:22,998 --> 00:39:26,351
If you let me again, master,
I'll make it more better.

285
00:40:38,341 --> 00:40:40,486
That's a really good perfume.

286
00:40:47,106 --> 00:40:49,216
Don't you want
to smell it, master?

287
00:40:49,267 --> 00:40:51,023
I'm not in the mood
to test it now.

288
00:40:51,072 --> 00:40:53,765
I have other things
on my mind. Go now.

289
00:40:55,553 --> 00:40:57,984
- But, master...
- Go now!

290
00:41:12,624 --> 00:41:15,524
Can't I come to work
for you, master, can't I?

291
00:41:17,635 --> 00:41:19,698
- Let me think about it.
- Master!

292
00:41:21,311 --> 00:41:24,315
I have to learn
how to keep smell.

293
00:41:25,743 --> 00:41:29,962
- What?
- Can you teach me that?

294
00:41:30,478 --> 00:41:32,661
I shall have to think
about it. Now go.

295
00:42:17,158 --> 00:42:18,672
I love you.

296
00:42:24,944 --> 00:42:27,377
I'll give you 50 francs for him.

297
00:42:34,429 --> 00:42:35,988
Grenouille!

298
00:42:36,030 --> 00:42:39,731
Grimal's transaction had
a profound effect on all three parties.

299
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:40,811
Hey, watch out!

300
00:42:44,378 --> 00:42:47,370
Now at least, upon
Monsieur Grimal himself.

301
00:42:50,131 --> 00:42:51,831
As for Giuseppe Baldini,

302
00:42:51,899 --> 00:42:56,423
the acquisition of Grenouille miraculously
transformed his dwindling business,

303
00:42:56,489 --> 00:42:59,315
even surpassing
its former glory.

304
00:43:07,038 --> 00:43:09,094
While at last, for Jean-Baptiste,

305
00:43:09,408 --> 00:43:13,979
the mysterious secret
of the perfumers' craft began to unfold.

306
00:43:20,088 --> 00:43:22,570
Now, pay careful attention
to what I tell you.

307
00:43:22,620 --> 00:43:24,088
Just like a musical cord,

308
00:43:24,146 --> 00:43:27,899
a perfume cord contains
four essences, or notes,

309
00:43:27,958 --> 00:43:31,085
carefully selected
for their harmonic affinity.

310
00:43:31,142 --> 00:43:36,386
Each perfume contains three cords:
the head, the heart and the base,

311
00:43:36,423 --> 00:43:38,972
necessitating twelve notes in all.

312
00:43:39,567 --> 00:43:42,470
The head cord contains
the first impression,

313
00:43:42,528 --> 00:43:45,992
lasting only a few minutes,
before giving way to the heart cord:

314
00:43:46,050 --> 00:43:49,646
the theme of the perfume,
lasting several hours.

315
00:43:49,684 --> 00:43:52,307
Finally, the base cord:

316
00:43:52,627 --> 00:43:56,318
the trail of the perfume,
lasting several days.

317
00:44:00,540 --> 00:44:05,309
Mind you, the ancient Egyptians believed
that one can only create a truly original perfume...

318
00:44:05,374 --> 00:44:11,744
by adding an extra note,
one final essence that will ring out...

319
00:44:12,234 --> 00:44:14,392
and dominate the others.

320
00:44:16,570 --> 00:44:20,972
Legend has it that a jar
was once found in a pharaoh's tomb.

321
00:44:21,072 --> 00:44:24,595
And when it was opened,
a perfume was released.

322
00:44:24,715 --> 00:44:27,615
After all those thousands of years,

323
00:44:27,675 --> 00:44:31,581
a perfume of such subtle beauty,
and yet such power,

324
00:44:31,671 --> 00:44:34,491
that for one single moment,

325
00:44:34,547 --> 00:44:38,970
every single person on earth
believed they were in paradise.

326
00:44:40,590 --> 00:44:43,275
Twelve essences
could be identified.

327
00:44:44,258 --> 00:44:47,956
But the thirteenth,
the vital one...

328
00:44:49,413 --> 00:44:51,509
could never be determined.

329
00:44:53,221 --> 00:44:54,036
Why not?

330
00:44:56,442 --> 00:44:57,022
Why not??

331
00:44:57,244 --> 00:44:58,777
What do you mean why not?

332
00:44:59,947 --> 00:45:02,435
Because it's a legend, numskull.

333
00:45:03,670 --> 00:45:04,823
What's a legend?

334
00:45:07,394 --> 00:45:08,311
Never mind.

335
00:45:48,890 --> 00:45:51,326
Jean-Baptiste. Jean-Baptiste.

336
00:45:56,946 --> 00:45:58,180
What's the matter?

337
00:45:58,734 --> 00:46:02,507
I... I have to learn
how to capture a scent.

338
00:46:05,077 --> 00:46:06,524
What are you talking about?

339
00:46:07,021 --> 00:46:11,578
I have to learn how... how to
capture a scent and "reprose" it forever.

340
00:46:11,823 --> 00:46:14,836
- You mean "preserve".
- Yes, teach me that.

341
00:46:15,186 --> 00:46:18,577
Calm down, my boy.
Calm down.

342
00:46:19,137 --> 00:46:20,678
We have work to do.

343
00:46:22,373 --> 00:46:27,554
The soul of beings is their scent.
You said that, master.

344
00:46:28,865 --> 00:46:29,749
Did I?

345
00:46:30,203 --> 00:46:34,062
I will make as many perfumes as you want.
But you have to teach me...

346
00:46:34,318 --> 00:46:36,895
how to capture
the smell of all things.

347
00:46:38,263 --> 00:46:39,582
Can you do that?

348
00:46:40,926 --> 00:46:45,258
- Well, naturally.
- Then teach me everything you know.

349
00:46:48,452 --> 00:46:50,900
And I'll make you the best perfumer
in the whole world.

350
00:47:08,070 --> 00:47:09,937
Imagine, Jean-Baptiste:

351
00:47:09,995 --> 00:47:16,354
ten thousand roses to produce
one single ounce of essential oil.

352
00:47:18,113 --> 00:47:24,001
Now, keep them flowing,
for the bottom petals will be given to stew,

353
00:47:24,239 --> 00:47:25,827
while I set up the alembic.

354
00:47:25,871 --> 00:47:27,663
And take care.
Not to damage them.

355
00:47:27,924 --> 00:47:31,655
We have to let them go to
their deaths with their scent intact.

356
00:47:49,424 --> 00:47:52,777
Perfect! Now, help me
with the boiler set.

357
00:48:05,620 --> 00:48:08,931
Temperature is vital.
When the quicksilver is here,

358
00:48:09,008 --> 00:48:13,702
the heat is precisely correct,
and the oil will gradually rise.

359
00:48:15,050 --> 00:48:20,410
Note that this mechanism is
a remarkable invention of my own devising.

360
00:48:20,954 --> 00:48:26,621
You will observe how cold water
is pumped through here,

361
00:48:27,252 --> 00:48:32,101
allowing the essence
to condense here...

362
00:48:32,157 --> 00:48:34,022
until it finally...

363
00:48:35,185 --> 00:48:36,482
appears...

364
00:48:37,958 --> 00:48:39,213
here!

365
00:48:40,153 --> 00:48:46,253
Of course, out on the hillside above Grasse,
we had only to bellow pure fresh air.

366
00:48:47,256 --> 00:48:50,250
Ah, Grasse! What a town.

367
00:48:52,220 --> 00:48:57,640
The Rome of scents.
The Promised Land of perfume.

368
00:48:58,984 --> 00:49:03,315
No man can rightly
call himself a perfumer,

369
00:49:03,662 --> 00:49:07,844
unless he has proved his worth
in that hallowed place.

370
00:49:10,176 --> 00:49:12,783
Not to worry!
It happens all the time.

371
00:49:14,356 --> 00:49:15,995
To Grasse.

372
00:49:33,226 --> 00:49:34,278
Master.

373
00:49:35,458 --> 00:49:36,432
Look.

374
00:49:41,631 --> 00:49:44,000
The very soul of the rose.

375
00:50:35,981 --> 00:50:37,629
Jean-Baptiste.

376
00:50:40,470 --> 00:50:41,447
What's wrong?

377
00:50:42,879 --> 00:50:44,251
Jean-Baptiste.

378
00:50:47,285 --> 00:50:50,070
- What have you done?
- You lied.

379
00:50:50,408 --> 00:50:53,512
- What?
- You lied to me.

380
00:50:54,117 --> 00:50:56,872
How dare you
talk to me like that!

381
00:50:58,281 --> 00:51:00,888
You said I could capture
the scent of anything.

382
00:51:01,661 --> 00:51:03,047
And so you can!

383
00:51:06,928 --> 00:51:08,123
What do you smell?

384
00:51:09,314 --> 00:51:10,713
What do you smell?

385
00:51:15,932 --> 00:51:16,611
Nothing.

386
00:51:20,013 --> 00:51:23,333
- What were you expecting to smell?
- Glass.

387
00:51:24,020 --> 00:51:27,932
- But glass doesn't smell.
- Of course it does. What's this?

388
00:51:32,988 --> 00:51:34,503
I don't smell a thing.

389
00:51:35,325 --> 00:51:36,016
Basta!

390
00:51:36,068 --> 00:51:38,358
- Did you smell that copper?
- Enough!

391
00:51:41,333 --> 00:51:44,775
You were trying to distil
the smell of copper?

392
00:51:45,275 --> 00:51:46,111
iron...

393
00:51:46,164 --> 00:51:47,129
glass...

394
00:51:47,591 --> 00:51:48,854
copper...

395
00:51:52,365 --> 00:51:54,013
What else did you try?

396
00:51:57,774 --> 00:51:58,530
No!

397
00:52:00,718 --> 00:52:02,666
Have you gone completely insane?!

398
00:52:03,611 --> 00:52:05,650
You told me I had to experiment.

399
00:52:05,925 --> 00:52:10,906
Experiment? Experiment?
With a cat?!

400
00:52:13,980 --> 00:52:15,806
What kind of a human being are youê é?

401
00:52:16,419 --> 00:52:17,977
Don't you know anything?

402
00:52:18,304 --> 00:52:20,452
You can no more distil
the scent of a cat...

403
00:52:20,506 --> 00:52:22,911
than you can distil
the scent of you and me!

404
00:52:33,426 --> 00:52:36,205
- I can't?
- Of course not!

405
00:52:43,153 --> 00:52:44,775
He's in stadio ultimo.

406
00:52:44,829 --> 00:52:46,284
- What?
- He's dying.

407
00:52:46,340 --> 00:52:47,832
Is there nothing you can do?

408
00:52:48,360 --> 00:52:51,415
- I fear not.
- No! He cannot die.

409
00:52:51,472 --> 00:52:55,374
- Well, the fee is 50 francs.
- 50 francs? You're a charlatan!

410
00:53:01,112 --> 00:53:05,111
Oh dear, Jean-Baptiste!

411
00:53:06,192 --> 00:53:10,258
You cannot do this to me.
Please, don't die on me.

412
00:53:10,592 --> 00:53:12,823
Not now, not yet!

413
00:53:23,813 --> 00:53:26,005
Is there...

414
00:53:29,647 --> 00:53:31,593
any other way...

415
00:53:32,889 --> 00:53:35,708
to preserve smell
besides distil it?

416
00:53:36,107 --> 00:53:37,851
Jean-Baptiste...

417
00:53:42,617 --> 00:53:48,500
- Is there, master?
- Well, yes, I... I believe there is.

418
00:53:49,909 --> 00:53:51,789
What is ité?

419
00:53:53,545 --> 00:53:57,503
It is known as
the mysterious art of Enfleurage.

420
00:53:59,894 --> 00:54:01,508
Can you teach me?

421
00:54:04,518 --> 00:54:07,708
Not even I am intimate
with the secrets.

422
00:54:10,365 --> 00:54:12,782
But could I learn it in Grasse?

423
00:54:13,886 --> 00:54:16,635
- Well...
- Could I?

424
00:54:22,374 --> 00:54:25,529
Where else but in Grasse!

425
00:54:31,142 --> 00:54:33,450
Within a week, Grenouille was well again.

426
00:54:33,802 --> 00:54:36,464
But in order to travel to Grasse,
and find a job,

427
00:54:36,506 --> 00:54:39,066
he needed a journeyman's papers.

428
00:54:39,302 --> 00:54:41,118
Baldini agreed to provide them,

429
00:54:41,445 --> 00:54:47,152
on condition that Grenouille left him
not less than 100 formulas for new perfumes.

430
00:54:47,952 --> 00:54:52,048
Grenouille did not mind.
He could've given him a thousand.

431
00:54:57,379 --> 00:55:01,281
The morning of Grenouille's departure,
Baldini was pleased.

432
00:55:01,725 --> 00:55:05,666
At last, he felt rewarded
for his many years of hard work.

433
00:55:06,186 --> 00:55:09,271
He could not remember
a happier day.

434
00:55:09,469 --> 00:55:12,271
Deeply satisfied, he went
back to sleep...

435
00:55:12,756 --> 00:55:15,718
and awoke no more
in this life.

436
00:55:33,991 --> 00:55:38,726
With every step Grenouille took away
from the city, the happier he felt.

437
00:55:39,172 --> 00:55:43,886
The air above him grew
clearer, purer, cleaner.

438
00:55:44,016 --> 00:55:47,089
And at last, he was
able to breathe freely.

439
00:55:50,447 --> 00:55:53,036
There were two ways
to reach Grasse.

440
00:55:53,237 --> 00:55:56,749
The first followed the winding road
through the villages...

441
00:55:56,750 --> 00:55:59,758
while the second lay straight across
the hills and mountains,

442
00:55:59,815 --> 00:56:01,925
down into Provence.

443
00:56:02,917 --> 00:56:05,183
The choice was quite easy.

444
00:56:08,905 --> 00:56:13,734
Thus, his nose led him ever higher,
ever further from mankind.

445
00:56:14,137 --> 00:56:19,472
Ever more towards the magnetic pole
of the greatest possible solitude.

446
00:56:56,624 --> 00:56:57,997
Grenouille needed a moment...

447
00:56:58,049 --> 00:57:00,969
to believe that he had actually
found a spot on earth...

448
00:57:01,003 --> 00:57:03,824
where scent was almost absent.

449
00:57:08,825 --> 00:57:10,036
Spread all around...

450
00:57:10,099 --> 00:57:13,177
lay nothing but the tranquil
scent of dead stone.

451
00:57:16,372 --> 00:57:19,450
There was something
sacred about this place.

452
00:57:22,965 --> 00:57:25,571
No longer distracted
by anything external,

453
00:57:26,294 --> 00:57:30,851
he was finally able
to bask in his own existence.

454
00:57:32,264 --> 00:57:35,462
And found it splendid!

455
00:57:42,413 --> 00:57:46,669
After a while, he almost forgot
his plans and obsessions.

456
00:57:47,994 --> 00:57:51,493
And indeed,
might've done so altogether.

457
00:58:05,873 --> 00:58:07,051
Helloá.

458
00:58:10,996 --> 00:58:12,355
Helloá.

459
00:58:14,990 --> 00:58:16,438
Helloá.

460
00:58:33,235 --> 00:58:35,965
There were a thousand smells
in his clothes.

461
00:58:36,028 --> 00:58:38,942
The smell of sand, stone, moss...

462
00:58:38,981 --> 00:58:41,512
even the smell of the sausage
he'd eaten weeks ago.

463
00:58:41,982 --> 00:58:44,357
Only one smell was not there:

464
00:58:47,540 --> 00:58:48,977
His own.

465
00:59:24,504 --> 00:59:27,064
For the first time in his life,
Grenouille realized...

466
00:59:27,124 --> 00:59:29,623
that he had no smell of his own.

467
00:59:30,889 --> 00:59:32,376
He realized that all his life...

468
00:59:32,452 --> 00:59:34,800
he had been a nobody
to everyone.

469
00:59:35,995 --> 00:59:39,674
What he now felt
was the fear of his own oblivion.

470
00:59:40,359 --> 00:59:41,981
It was as though...

471
00:59:42,144 --> 00:59:44,022
he did not exist.

472
00:59:49,202 --> 00:59:53,347
By the first light of next morning,
Grenouille had a new plan.

473
00:59:53,737 --> 00:59:56,550
He must continue
his journey to Grasse.

474
00:59:56,870 --> 01:00:00,267
There he would teach the world
not only that he existed...

475
01:00:00,338 --> 01:00:01,966
that he was someone...

476
01:00:02,293 --> 01:00:04,796
but that he was exceptional.

477
01:00:08,676 --> 01:00:10,326
And with this decision,

478
01:00:10,729 --> 01:00:14,832
it seemed that the gods
had at last begun to smile on him.

479
01:04:31,357 --> 01:04:32,621
Laura?

480
01:04:40,006 --> 01:04:41,241
Laura?

481
01:04:42,018 --> 01:04:43,784
Coming, papa.

482
01:05:18,875 --> 01:05:21,142
Haven't seen you here before.

483
01:05:22,623 --> 01:05:24,292
It's my first season.

484
01:05:25,721 --> 01:05:27,790
Picking together
is always more fun.

485
01:05:29,134 --> 01:05:31,277
They say you pick
everything you find.

486
01:06:13,916 --> 01:06:17,845
Idiot! How many times do I told you
not to cram the blossoms in...

487
01:06:17,881 --> 01:06:19,568
like you're stuffing a chicken?

488
01:06:21,039 --> 01:06:22,733
Watch how Grenouille does it.

489
01:06:24,706 --> 01:06:28,647
Look how skillfully he handles them.
The whole art of Enflourage...

490
01:06:28,685 --> 01:06:32,607
is to allow the flowers to die slowly,
in their sleep as it were...

491
01:06:32,934 --> 01:06:37,687
handle them as you would a lady.
Wouldn't you agree with me, Druot?

492
01:06:38,136 --> 01:06:39,910
If you say so, madame.

493
01:06:42,433 --> 01:06:45,021
You! Check the jonquil blossoms.

494
01:06:48,407 --> 01:06:50,006
It need more time.

495
01:06:52,494 --> 01:06:54,199
Do what I say.

496
01:07:36,582 --> 01:07:37,781
Stop it!

497
01:07:38,679 --> 01:07:40,014
I'm not in the mood.

498
01:07:40,433 --> 01:07:41,620
Are you sure?

499
01:07:42,585 --> 01:07:44,219
Of course I'm sure.

500
01:07:50,275 --> 01:07:51,824
I said...

