as soon as possible.

755
01:42:31,942 --> 01:42:34,876
Until then, you stay
in the safety of the monastery.

756
01:42:36,576 --> 01:42:41,111
- And all this, because you had a bad dream?
- I've made my decision.

757
01:42:41,224 --> 01:42:45,306
- But I don't know whether I even love him!
- I'm afraid the circumstances leave us no choice.

758
01:42:45,384 --> 01:42:47,975
- Papa!
- It's all arranged, Laura.

759
01:48:23,606 --> 01:48:24,644
On your feet!

760
01:48:25,188 --> 01:48:26,185
Hands in the air!

761
01:49:10,282 --> 01:49:12,779
Why did you kill my daughter?

762
01:49:16,732 --> 01:49:17,783
Why?

763
01:49:20,958 --> 01:49:22,389
I needed her.

764
01:49:47,678 --> 01:49:49,917
Why did you kill my daughter?

765
01:49:54,185 --> 01:49:55,741
I just...

766
01:49:58,353 --> 01:49:59,823
needed her.

767
01:50:07,288 --> 01:50:08,551
Very well.

768
01:50:10,666 --> 01:50:12,895
But you remember this:

769
01:50:19,209 --> 01:50:21,030
I'll be looking at you...

770
01:50:23,575 --> 01:50:25,087
when you're laid on the cross,

771
01:50:25,150 --> 01:50:29,638
and the twelve blows are
crashing down on your limbs.

772
01:50:31,773 --> 01:50:37,175
When the crowd is finally tired
of your screams and wandered home...

773
01:50:38,346 --> 01:50:42,469
I will climb up
through your blood...

774
01:50:44,233 --> 01:50:46,413
and sit beside you.

775
01:50:47,992 --> 01:50:51,438
I will look deep
into your eyes...

776
01:50:52,431 --> 01:50:55,479
and drop by drop...

777
01:50:57,348 --> 01:51:01,192
I will trickle my digust into them...

778
01:51:02,864 --> 01:51:05,721
like burning acid...

779
01:51:07,467 --> 01:51:08,870
until...

780
01:51:12,250 --> 01:51:13,706
finally...

781
01:51:17,193 --> 01:51:19,226
you perish.

782
01:51:53,119 --> 01:51:54,642
What do you think
they'll do to him?

783
01:51:54,922 --> 01:51:58,650
Apparently, they're gonna break
every bone in his body with an iron bar.

784
01:52:11,482 --> 01:52:12,856
Look, there he comes!

785
01:53:14,149 --> 01:53:15,648
Unchain the prisoner.

786
01:53:26,645 --> 01:53:28,174
That's enough.

787
01:53:29,599 --> 01:53:31,520
Let him be brought
to the scaffold.

788
01:53:36,419 --> 01:53:37,347
What's that?

789
01:54:48,386 --> 01:54:50,104
Is he coming? What's his name?

790
01:56:35,659 --> 01:56:38,586
This man is innocent.

791
01:56:42,323 --> 01:56:45,026
- He didn't do it. It's impossible!
- He's innocent!

792
01:56:49,286 --> 01:56:50,513
He's innocent!

793
01:58:07,453 --> 01:58:11,635
This is no man!
This is an angel!

794
02:04:04,931 --> 02:04:07,147
You can't fool me!

795
02:04:53,946 --> 02:04:55,479
Forgive me!

796
02:05:01,869 --> 02:05:03,946
My son!

797
02:06:03,944 --> 02:06:07,769
People of Grasse
awoke to a terrible hangover.

798
02:06:09,034 --> 02:06:14,048
For many of them, the experience
was so gustly, so completely inexplicable...

799
02:06:14,080 --> 02:06:20,013
and incompatible with their morals,
that they literally erased it from their memories.

800
02:06:20,632 --> 02:06:23,505
The town council
was in session by the afternoon.

801
02:06:23,624 --> 02:06:29,527
And an order was passed to the police lieutenant
to immediately begin fresh investigations into the murders.

802
02:06:30,628 --> 02:06:33,536
The following day, Dominique Druot
was arrested.

803
02:06:33,619 --> 02:06:38,189
Since it was in his backyard that the clothes
and hair of all the victims had been found.

804
02:06:39,164 --> 02:06:42,452
After fourteen hours of torture,
Druot confessed to everything.

805
02:06:45,170 --> 02:06:47,723
With that, the case was closed.

806
02:06:51,911 --> 02:06:55,587
By then, Grenouille was already
halfway back to Paris.

807
02:06:59,404 --> 02:07:03,566
He still had enough perfume left
to enslave the whole world, if he so chose.

808
02:07:04,249 --> 02:07:07,357
He could walk to Versailles,
and have the King kiss his feet.

809
02:07:07,762 --> 02:07:12,113
He could write the Pope a perfumed letter,
and reveal himself as a new Messiah.

810
02:07:12,900 --> 02:07:15,834
He could do all this,
and more if he wanted to.

811
02:07:16,529 --> 02:07:20,976
He possessed a power stronger
than the power of money, or terror, or death.

812
02:07:21,734 --> 02:07:25,446
The invincible power
to command the love of mankind.

813
02:07:31,932 --> 02:07:34,703
There was only one thing
the perfume could not do.

814
02:07:35,084 --> 02:07:40,243
It could not turn him into a person
who could love and be loved like everyone else.

815
02:07:41,426 --> 02:07:45,178
So, to hell with it, he thought.
To hell with the world.

816
02:07:45,654 --> 02:07:48,556
With the perfume, with himself.

817
02:07:51,237 --> 02:07:56,306
On the 25th of June, 1766,
around 11 o'clock at night,

818
02:07:56,533 --> 02:07:59,618
Grenouille entered the city
through the port-de-Leones.

819
02:08:00,150 --> 02:08:06,865
And like a sleepwalker, his olfactory memories
drew him back to the place where he was born.

820
02:09:25,693 --> 02:09:28,410
An angel!

821
02:09:29,792 --> 02:09:31,697
I love you!

822
02:10:17,049 --> 02:10:22,545
Within no time, Jean-Baptiste Grenouille
had disappeared from the face of the earth.

823
02:10:23,546 --> 02:10:28,186
When they had finished,
they felt a virginal glow of happiness.

824
02:10:28,873 --> 02:10:33,951
For the first time in their lives,
they believed that they had done something...

825
02:10:34,185 --> 02:10:37,412
purely out of love.

826
02:11:06,900 --> 02:11:08,866
Hey, over here!

827
02:11:09,431 --> 02:11:10,385
Look!

828
02:11:17,407 --> 02:11:18,645
Let's take them away.

829
02:11:19,425 --> 02:11:20,537
You could wear them.

830
02:11:39,506 --> 02:11:44,134
*Sync KOz*

